    "text": "Donate\nFor every $1 donated, we can provide 9 meals. It’s that easy to make a difference!\nDonate Now\nVolunteer\nGo behind the scenes and get hands-on with hunger-relief efforts.\nRegister\nGet Involved\nAdvocate for those who otherwise wouldn’t have a voice.\nI’m Ready\nSpecial Initiatives\nThere’s always a different way to get involved depending on the season.\nExplore\nFeed\nHunger knows no age. Learn more about the programs nourishing every age group, from children in school to seniors in need.\nLearn more\nLead\nJoin us and be the voice that inspires change. Learn how to lead your community and fulfill the mission to end hunger in South Florida.\nLearn more\nStrengthen\nWe connect individuals with the training and resources necessary to increase family stability through economic self‑sufficiency.\nLearn more\nBy The Numbers:\n1074702\nFood insecure individuals\n329423\nChildren who go to bed hungry\n174500000\nMillion pounds of food distributed\n145700000\nMillion meals distributed\nSEARCH NOW\nChuck Woods, our Director of Food Supply Chain, was honored at the Hats, Heels, and Bowties event hosted by The Links, in November, for…\nRead More\nWhen children are properly nourished, they thrive in the classroom and can achieve so much more outside of school, at home and beyond. Feeding…\nRead More\nSeptember is Hunger Action Month®. GO ORANGE and help us take a stand against hunger within the South Florida community. GO ORANGE How can…\nRead More\nKEY LARGO – Feeding South Florida partnered with Monroe County Social Services to host a free food distribution event Friday, Feb. 2S, at Tradewinds…\nRead More\nPEMBROKE PARK, FLA. (WSVN) – A South Florida organization continues to feed creativity. Feeding South Florida announced its third annual Feed Your Creativity art…\nRead More\nMajority are working families attending giveaway events, Feeding South Florida president says. BOYNTON BEACH, Fla. — Cars were lined up for more than 12 hours Thursday…\nRead More\n\n\n\n\nSITE LINKS\nDONATE NOW\nVOLUNTEER\nGET HELP\nCONTACT US\nEVENTS\nPRESS ROOM\nCAREERS\nFORM 990\nAUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS\nLOCATIONS\nMain Warehouse\n2501 SW 32 Terrace\nPembroke Park, FL 33023\n954.518.1818\nFeeding Palm Beach County\n4925 Park Ridge Blvd\nBoynton Beach, FL 33426\n561.331.5441\n© Feeding South Florida is a 501 (c)(3). © 2019 All rights reserved.\nTranslate »",
